    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen running certain commands like `:hi` or `:au`, the output will include an empty newline before any output.\n\n<img width=\"865\" height=\"561\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/49eb9e1a-190d-4fa0-b78a-432b597b8565\" />\n\n<img width=\"865\" height=\"561\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6f0ee3f9-3ce4-4a05-b97a-322a2c7fc2a1\" />\n\nThis even happens when the command is only one line long and the pager should not be opened, for example, with `:hi @attribute`:\n\n<img width=\"865\" height=\"561\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/9919aa60-f1a8-466d-91c5-2041ff0ec4b3\" />\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- `nvim --clean`\n- `:lua require('vim._extui').enable {}`\n- Run a command like `:hi` or `:au`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThere is not a blank newline at the top.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev+2173-d59440773, although this has existed for a while. I just never reported it until now.\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnot applicable\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFedora 43\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.43.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nFedora COPR",
